The position vectors of the points A, B, C and D are $$3\widehat i - 2\widehat j - \widehat k$$, $$2\widehat i - 3\widehat j + 2\widehat k$$, $$5\widehat i - \widehat j + 2\widehat k$$ and $$4\widehat i - \widehat j - \lambda \widehat k$$ respectively.<br><br>$$BA = (3\widehat i - 2\widehat j - \widehat k) - (2\widehat i - 3\widehat j + 2\widehat k) = \widehat i + \widehat j - 3\widehat k$$<br><br>$$CA = (3\widehat i - 2\widehat j - \widehat k) - (5\widehat i - \widehat j + 2\widehat k) =  - 2\widehat i - \widehat j - 3\widehat k$$<br><br>$$DA = (3\widehat i - 2\widehat j - \widehat k) - (4\widehat i - \widehat j + \lambda \widehat k)$$<br><br>$$ =  - \widehat i - \widehat j - (1 + \lambda )\widehat k$$<br><br>These are coplanar, so<br><br>$$\left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; { - 3}  \cr 
   { - 2} &amp; { - 1} &amp; { - 3}  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; { - 1} &amp; { - (1 + \lambda )}  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$ = \left| {\matrix{
   { - 1} &amp; { - 1} &amp; 3  \cr 
   2 &amp; 1 &amp; 3  \cr 
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; {1 + \lambda }  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$ - 1[1 + \lambda  - 3] + 1[2 + 2\lambda  - 3] + 3[2 - 1] = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow  - 1[\lambda  - 2] + 1[2\lambda  - 1] + 3 = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow  - \lambda  + 2 + 2\lambda  - 1 + 3 = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \lambda  + 4 = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \lambda  =  - 4$$
